Menu="NetworkServices"
Title="WG Watchdog"
Icon="shield"
Tag="shield"
---
<?php
$plugin = "wg-watchdog";
$cfg    = parse_plugin_cfg($plugin);

$defaults = [
    'SERVICE_ENABLED' => 'no',
    'INTERFACE'       => 'wg0',
    'PEER_IP'         => '10.99.0.1',
    'INTERVAL'        => '60',
    'VERBOSE'         => 'no',
    'LOG_FILE'        => '/var/log/wg-watchdog.log',
];
foreach ($defaults as $k => $v) {
    if (!isset($cfg[$k]) || $cfg[$k] === '') $cfg[$k] = $v;
}
?>

<form markdown="1" method="POST" action="/plugins/wg-watchdog/include/apply.php" target="progressFrame">

_(Enabled)_:
: <select name="SERVICE_ENABLED">
  <?=mk_option($cfg['SERVICE_ENABLED'], "no",  _("No"))?>
  <?=mk_option($cfg['SERVICE_ENABLED'], "yes", _("Yes"))?>
  </select>

<blockquote class="inline_help">
When disabled, the watchdog cron entry is removed and no checks run.
</blockquote>

_(Tunnel interface)_:
: <input type="text" name="INTERFACE" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($cfg['INTERFACE'])?>" placeholder="wg0">

<blockquote class="inline_help">
The WireGuard interface to monitor (e.g. wg0, wg1). Managed by the
Unraid WireGuard plugin -- this watchdog only calls wg-quick down/up.
</blockquote>

_(Peer IP to ping)_:
: <input type="text" name="PEER_IP" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($cfg['PEER_IP'])?>" placeholder="10.99.0.1">

<blockquote class="inline_help">
An IP reachable through the tunnel -- typically the remote peer's
internal address.
</blockquote>

_(Check interval)_:
: <input type="number" name="INTERVAL" min="20" step="1" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($cfg['INTERVAL'])?>" style="width:6em;"> _(seconds, minimum 20)_

<blockquote class="inline_help">
Below 60s the cron file is generated as multiple per-minute lines with
sleep offsets.
</blockquote>

_(Verbose logging)_:
: <select name="VERBOSE">
  <?=mk_option($cfg['VERBOSE'], "no",  _("No"))?>
  <?=mk_option($cfg['VERBOSE'], "yes", _("Yes"))?>
  </select>

<blockquote class="inline_help">
If yes, every successful ping is logged. Otherwise only failures and
recovery actions are logged.
</blockquote>

_(Log file)_:
: <input type="text" readonly value="<?=htmlspecialchars($cfg['LOG_FILE'])?>" style="width:24em;background:#eee;">

&nbsp;
: <input type="submit" name="#apply" value="_(Apply)_">
  <input type="button" value="_(Test Now)_" onclick="wgTest()">
  <input type="button" value="_(View Log)_" onclick="wgLog()">

</form>

<div id="wg-watchdog-output"
     style="display:none;white-space:pre-wrap;font-family:monospace;background:#111;color:#eee;padding:10px;margin-top:10px;max-height:420px;overflow:auto;border-radius:4px;"></div>

<script>
function wgWatchdogShow(text) {
    var out = document.getElementById('wg-watchdog-output');
    out.style.display = 'block';
    out.textContent = text;
}
function wgTest() {
    wgWatchdogShow('Running test...');
    fetch('/plugins/wg-watchdog/include/test.php', {method:'POST', credentials:'same-origin'})
        .then(function(r){ return r.text(); })
        .then(function(t){ wgWatchdogShow(t || '(no output)'); })
        .catch(function(e){ wgWatchdogShow('Error: ' + e); });
}
function wgLog() {
    wgWatchdogShow('Loading log...');
    fetch('/plugins/wg-watchdog/include/log.php', {credentials:'same-origin'})
        .then(function(r){ return r.text(); })
        .then(function(t){ wgWatchdogShow(t || '(log empty)'); })
        .catch(function(e){ wgWatchdogShow('Error: ' + e); });
}
</script>
